tain in Iwate Prefecture, is on the border of Hachimantai with Shizukuishi and Takizawa.\n\n===Neighboring municipalities===\nAomori Prefecture\n*[[Takko, Aomori|Takko]]\nAkita Prefecture\n*[[Kazuno, Akita|Kazuno]]\n*[[Semboku, Akita|Semboku]]\nIwate Prefecture\n*[[Morioka, Iwate|Morioka]]\n*[[Ninohe, Iwate|Ninohe]]\n*[[Takizawa, Iwate|Takizawa]]\n*[[Ichinohe, Iwate|Ichinohe]]\n*[[Iwate, Iwate|Iwate]]\n*[[Shizukuishi, Iwate|Shizukuishi]]\n\n===Climate===\nHachimantai has a [[humid continental climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]] ''Dfa''), the same as much of [[Hokkaido]] to the north, characterized by mild summers and cold winters with heavy snowfall. The average annual temperature in Hachimantai is 9.3&nbsp;\u00b0C. The average annual rainfall is 1387&nbsp;mm with September as the wettest month and February as the driest month. The temperatures are highest on average in August, at around 22.9&nbsp;\u00b0C, and lowest in January, at around -3.4&nbsp;\u00b0C.<ref>[https://en.climate-data.org/location/5525/ Hachimantai climate data]</ref>\n\n{{Weather box|width=auto\n|location = Hachimantai (former Matsuo Village\u30011981-2010)\n|metric first = yes\n|single line = yes\n|Jan record high C = 12.4\n|Feb record high C = 12.0\n|Mar record high C = 18.0\n|Apr record high C = 27.7\n|May record high C = 31.8\n|Jun record high C = 33.5\n|Jul record high C = 35.2\n|Aug record high C = 35.5\n|Sep record high C = 34.0\n|Oct record high C = 26.5\n|Nov record high C = 20.7\n|Dec record high C = 16.9\n|Jan high C = 0.6\n|Feb high C = 1.6\n|Mar high C = 5.7\n|Apr high C = 13.7 \n|May high C = 19.3\n|Jun high C = 23.3\n|Jul high C = 26.2\n|Aug high C = 27.8\n|Sep high C = 22.9\n|Oct high C = 16.9\n|Nov high C = 9.7\n|Dec high C = 3.6\n|year high C = 14.2\n|Jan mean C = -3.4\n|Feb mean C = -2.8\n|Mar mean C = 0.9\n|Apr mean C = 7.6\n|May mean C = 13.3\n|Jun mean C = 17.6\n|Jul mean C = 21.1\n|Aug mean C = 22.4\n|Sep mean C = 17.5\n|Oct mean C = 10.9\n|Nov mean C = 4.7\n|D